WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:03.880
Yes, Dad,
I saw the article you sent.

00:03.880 --> 00:05.710
I've just been busy.

00:05.710 --> 00:08.960
No, they're not overworking me,
but I'm an intern,

00:08.960 --> 00:11.710
so I kinda have to do,
like, everything.

00:11.710 --> 00:12.710
[ Scoffs ]

00:12.710 --> 00:14.040
President?

00:14.040 --> 00:16.000
I don't know, Dad.

00:16.000 --> 00:17.830
Okay, I gotta go.

00:17.830 --> 00:20.500
I'll talk to you later.

00:20.500 --> 00:22.710
Love you, too.

00:22.710 --> 00:25.080
♪♪

00:25.080 --> 00:27.080
Can I help you?

00:27.080 --> 00:28.580
I need a gun.

00:28.580 --> 00:30.170
You got ID?

00:33.250 --> 00:35.380
So what kind of gun
you want?

00:35.380 --> 00:37.620
One that works.

00:45.040 --> 00:46.330
[ Knock on door ]

00:49.960 --> 00:51.290
I have nothing
to say to you.

00:51.290 --> 00:54.120
It's about the hijacking.
It was Cyrus.

00:54.120 --> 00:56.620
Cyrus Beene hijacked
his own plane for attention?

00:56.620 --> 00:58.290
He wants to be
President.

00:58.290 --> 01:00.000
The election's not
for another three years.

01:00.000 --> 01:01.290
Seven
if Mellie runs again.

01:01.290 --> 01:03.080
I don't think
he wants to wait that long.

01:03.080 --> 01:05.460
Cyrus wants the Oval.
He wants it now.

01:05.460 --> 01:07.620
We need to figure out
how he's going to take that,

01:07.620 --> 01:08.790
and what it means
for Mellie.

01:08.790 --> 01:10.710
-We?
-The team.

01:10.710 --> 01:12.040
You don't have a team.

01:12.040 --> 01:13.790
I know that.

01:13.790 --> 01:15.830
No, you don't. If you did,
you wouldn't come to my home,

01:15.830 --> 01:17.380
asking for favors.
-Abby --

01:17.380 --> 01:20.000
If I went to QPA with this and
told them that it came from you?

01:20.000 --> 01:21.250
I'd be out on my ass, too.

01:21.250 --> 01:23.170
That's how much they don't
want to hear from you.

01:23.170 --> 01:24.380
I understand
what you're saying.

01:24.380 --> 01:27.920
I wouldn't be here
if I had another option.

01:27.920 --> 01:31.080
I'm not asking for forgiveness,
I'm asking for help.

01:31.080 --> 01:32.710
I need help.

01:32.710 --> 01:34.000
Please.

01:34.000 --> 01:36.040
♪♪

01:36.040 --> 01:37.790
I'll see what I can do.

01:37.790 --> 01:40.170
And then, if this theory
of yours proves to be true,

01:40.170 --> 01:42.540
the team will decide whether
it's a fight worth fighting.

01:42.540 --> 01:46.750
♪♪

01:46.750 --> 01:48.250
Madam President?

01:48.250 --> 01:50.330
Mellie: Down here.

01:55.790 --> 01:58.380
I tweaked my back.
Can you believe it?

01:58.380 --> 02:00.620
The doctor gave me
a tennis ball, some Tylenol,

02:00.620 --> 02:01.790
and said, "Good luck."

02:01.790 --> 02:03.210
President
of the United States.

02:03.210 --> 02:05.380
Short of overhauling
the country's medical training,

02:05.380 --> 02:07.170
how can I help?
-The federal budget.

02:07.170 --> 02:08.710
We're facing
a government shutdown

02:08.710 --> 02:10.170
if we can't get the votes
in Congress.

02:10.170 --> 02:12.040
You want to use B613
to dig up some dirt?

02:12.040 --> 02:14.920
No. Threatening people
creates resentment.

02:14.920 --> 02:17.040
I don't just want votes,
I want support,

02:17.040 --> 02:18.620
and there's an easier way.

02:18.620 --> 02:20.170
[ Gasps, sighs ]

02:20.170 --> 02:21.710
We need Cyrus.

02:21.710 --> 02:22.830
Madam President --

02:22.830 --> 02:25.000
He's dominating in the polls
right now.

02:25.000 --> 02:27.210
We'd be foolish
not to take advantage of it.

02:27.210 --> 02:28.710
I'd prefer we find
another way.

02:28.710 --> 02:30.380
And I'd prefer
to be on my feet,

02:30.380 --> 02:32.120
but until a better option
presents itself...

02:32.120 --> 02:33.380
[ Sighs ]

02:33.380 --> 02:34.750
...you got to let
your grudge match go.

02:34.750 --> 02:36.710
We need him.

02:36.710 --> 02:38.750
Yes, Madam President.

02:38.750 --> 02:40.080
Filiz:
This thing's a mess.

02:40.080 --> 02:41.420
The computer virus
that managed

02:41.420 --> 02:43.290
to circumvent
all our safety protocols

02:43.290 --> 02:45.000
and take control
of the Vice President's plane

02:45.000 --> 02:46.290
is a mess?

02:46.290 --> 02:48.710
A total hack job.
It's got syntax errors,

02:48.710 --> 02:52.170
recursion loops, it leaks memory
like the Exxon Valdez.

02:52.170 --> 02:53.460
I could cross-reference
the code

02:53.460 --> 02:55.080
with the code
of all known hackers,

02:55.080 --> 02:56.620
but that would be
a waste of time.

02:56.620 --> 02:58.790
No self-respecting coder
did this.

02:58.790 --> 03:00.920
-So who did?
-There are two possibilities.

03:00.920 --> 03:03.330
Either the coder is new --
like grade-school new --

03:03.330 --> 03:05.040
or they did a crappy job
on purpose

03:05.040 --> 03:06.960
so the code would be
impenetrable,

03:06.960 --> 03:08.790
which would make them
a secret genius.

03:08.790 --> 03:12.040
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:12.040 --> 03:13.790
Liv.

03:13.790 --> 03:15.420
It's late. What's up?

03:15.420 --> 03:17.580
Not much. I was thinking about
grabbing some dinner.

03:17.580 --> 03:19.170
Interested?

03:19.170 --> 03:21.250
You really don't have
any other friends, do you?

03:21.250 --> 03:23.380
No. Not really.

03:23.380 --> 03:25.580
Although I did talk
to Abby today.

03:25.580 --> 03:28.420
She even invited me into her
apartment, so that's something.

03:28.420 --> 03:30.000
Yeah?
What did you talk about?

03:31.920 --> 03:33.420
Nothing. [ Scoffs ]

03:33.420 --> 03:34.540
[ Knock on door ]

03:34.540 --> 03:35.920
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

03:35.920 --> 03:38.580
I waited in reception but there
wasn't anyone at the desk.

03:38.580 --> 03:39.960
Well, it's actually
after hours,

03:39.960 --> 03:41.210
so if you
want to come back --

03:41.210 --> 03:43.250
-You're Olivia Pope.
-I am.

03:43.250 --> 03:45.620
You're the person
I'm looking for.

03:45.620 --> 03:47.790
♪♪

03:47.790 --> 03:51.290
Alisha's only 21.
No one's seen her in days.

03:51.290 --> 03:53.170
Her roommate doesn't
know anything,

03:53.170 --> 03:55.790
and the cops say it's too soon
to call her a missing person.

03:55.790 --> 03:57.960
I-I don't know this city.
[ Chuckles ]

03:57.960 --> 04:00.920
It's the first time I've set
foot outside Ohio in 10 years.

04:00.920 --> 04:04.500
Gary. I'm sorry,
but this is not what I do.

04:04.500 --> 04:07.210
Not anymore.
However, I am sure th--

04:07.210 --> 04:09.420
She's here because
of you.

04:09.420 --> 04:11.670
-What do you mean?
-She idolizes you.

04:11.670 --> 04:13.500
She's watched you
for years on TV

04:13.500 --> 04:15.330
speaking for members
of Congress,

04:15.330 --> 04:17.500
senators, Presidents.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.210
[ Chuckles ]

04:19.210 --> 04:21.210
A woman who looks
like her.

04:21.210 --> 04:23.500
You're the reason she
fell in love with politics.

04:23.500 --> 04:25.460
You're the reason
she came to D.C.,

04:25.460 --> 04:27.460
the reason she became
a Congressional intern.

04:27.460 --> 04:31.710
A-And she's doing so well.
I'm -- I'm so proud.

04:31.710 --> 04:35.670
I-If you could see how hard
she works, how smart she is,

04:35.670 --> 04:37.920
you'd be proud [scoffs] to have
someone like Alisha

04:37.920 --> 04:39.290
following in
your footsteps.

04:39.290 --> 04:42.170
But something happened.

04:42.170 --> 04:46.040
She hasn't called me in a week,
and it's not like her.

04:46.040 --> 04:47.880
Something's wrong.

04:47.880 --> 04:50.540
I...know it in my gut.

04:50.540 --> 04:53.330
♪♪

04:53.330 --> 04:56.170
Alisha came here
because of you,

04:56.170 --> 05:00.080
and now I'm here
because of you.

05:00.080 --> 05:01.790
Please.

05:01.790 --> 05:04.380
Help me find my daughter.

05:04.380 --> 05:07.120
♪♪

05:11.960 --> 05:14.460
Alisha Francis.
21-year-old Georgetown senior

05:14.460 --> 05:16.330
majoring
in Government Affairs.

05:16.330 --> 05:18.670
Since the summer,
she's been interning

05:18.670 --> 05:20.830
in the office of Ohio
Congressman Philip Beard.

05:20.830 --> 05:22.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

05:22.250 --> 05:24.330
Her father hasn't heard
from her for a week.

05:24.330 --> 05:26.420
Have you spoken to anyone in
Congressman Beard's office?

05:26.420 --> 05:28.420
I tried them, but I just
got the runaround.

05:28.420 --> 05:31.040
You think
there's a case there?

05:31.040 --> 05:34.080
I know this isn't
exactly what we do, but...

05:35.670 --> 05:37.250
Okay.

05:37.250 --> 05:39.710
I'll head to her apartment.
See what I can find.

05:39.710 --> 05:41.250
I'll reach out
to Metro Police.

05:41.250 --> 05:43.170
They're getting pretty
accustomed to hearing from me.

05:43.170 --> 05:47.170
♪♪

05:47.170 --> 05:50.540
♪♪

05:50.540 --> 05:52.500
Thank you.

05:52.500 --> 05:55.920
♪♪

05:55.920 --> 05:58.830
Cyrus Beene, the Vice President
of the United States,

05:58.830 --> 06:00.790
hijacked his own plane?
That's --

06:00.790 --> 06:02.380
The plot
of a bad action movie?

06:02.380 --> 06:04.460
Now that I said it out loud,
yeah, I guess it kind of is,

06:04.460 --> 06:06.210
but that doesn't mean
it's not true.

06:06.210 --> 06:07.620
Well, where is this
coming from?

06:07.620 --> 06:09.830
I-Is it a hunch? Have you
been talking to someone?

06:09.830 --> 06:12.710
Just David. Something he told me
got me thinking.

06:12.710 --> 06:14.250
Something?

06:14.250 --> 06:16.040
He said Cyrus requested that
he go to Lisbon with him.

06:16.040 --> 06:17.790
Cyrus Beene,
my former boss --

06:17.790 --> 06:20.330
A man whose personal e-mail
still ends in "aol.com" --

06:20.330 --> 06:23.120
suddenly signs up for a digital
piracy summit an ocean away?

06:23.120 --> 06:24.790
Why would he do that?
Unless --

06:24.790 --> 06:26.580
He wanted to be
on Air Force Two.

06:26.580 --> 06:29.460
Excuse me. Before we all bust
out the tinfoil hats,

06:29.460 --> 06:31.290
do I need to remind
you people what happened

06:31.290 --> 06:33.330
the last time one of us ran up
a White House conspiracy

06:33.330 --> 06:34.790
involving a plane?
-Charlie.

06:34.790 --> 06:38.040
Quinn...can I speak
to you for a sec?

06:38.040 --> 06:39.080
Alone?

06:43.460 --> 06:46.080
Okay, talk.

06:46.080 --> 06:48.880
I lost you.
You were...dead.

06:48.880 --> 06:52.000
Yeah, but now I'm back,
and we have a job to do.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.580
Yes, I know.
But...going after Cyrus --

06:54.580 --> 06:57.250
Is exactly the kind of thing
we do here.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.380
Charlie,
if Abby is right,

06:59.380 --> 07:01.670
if Cyrus is up to something
and we do nothing?

07:01.670 --> 07:04.380
Then whatever happens next
will be on us.

07:04.380 --> 07:06.170
I didn't come back
to sit on the sidelines.

07:07.670 --> 07:09.920
[ Knock on door ]

07:11.250 --> 07:12.920
Olivia Pope.

07:12.920 --> 07:14.120
Yes, and you are?

07:14.120 --> 07:16.290
Meghan...Seeley. I...

07:16.290 --> 07:19.170
What are you
doing here?

07:19.170 --> 07:21.880
I'm looking
for Alisha Francis.

07:21.880 --> 07:23.880
You're Alisha's hero.

07:23.880 --> 07:26.290
Or, I guess heroine.

07:26.290 --> 07:28.920
You say she's been
gone a couple of days.

07:28.920 --> 07:33.120
She moped around for a day or so
after she lost her job,

07:33.120 --> 07:34.790
but I didn't see her
after that.

07:34.790 --> 07:37.000
I figured she went home
to her parents' place

07:37.000 --> 07:38.620
to lick her wounds.
-She lost her job when?

07:38.620 --> 07:40.790
Last week.

07:40.790 --> 07:44.620
She wouldn't have told you
if she were leaving town?

07:44.620 --> 07:47.580
We really just share the rent.
We're not super close.

07:47.580 --> 07:49.330
So then, she probably
didn't talk to you

07:49.330 --> 07:50.750
about how
she lost her job?

07:50.750 --> 07:53.540
[ Sighs ] Well, that's
actually kinda awkward.

07:53.540 --> 07:55.420
We've both been interning
for Congressman Beard.

07:55.420 --> 07:57.040
It's how we got matched
as roommates.

07:57.040 --> 07:58.710
When your internship
is over,

07:58.710 --> 08:01.080
they either hire you on
full-time or they say,

08:01.080 --> 08:03.540
"Thanks, but no thanks,"
and you have to figure out

08:03.540 --> 08:05.790
something else to do
with your life.

08:05.790 --> 08:09.170
I got hired, but Alisha...

08:09.170 --> 08:11.330
She didn't.

08:11.330 --> 08:12.960
Yeah.

08:12.960 --> 08:16.040
Speaking of,
I really should get to work.

08:16.040 --> 08:18.040
You go ahead,
finish getting ready.

08:18.040 --> 08:19.120
I'll walk out with you.

08:19.120 --> 08:23.250
♪♪

08:23.250 --> 08:28.120
♪♪

08:28.120 --> 08:30.250
Fitz: "I promise I didn't mean
to offend you,

08:30.250 --> 08:32.210
and I hope we can let
bygones be bygones.

08:32.210 --> 08:34.330
It's my dream to have
a career in Washington.

08:34.330 --> 08:37.080
I've worked too hard
to be GFV'ed for this.

08:37.080 --> 08:39.580
I'm not going to tell anyone
what happened.

08:39.580 --> 08:41.120
I hope you can do
the same for me."

08:41.120 --> 08:42.500
What's "GFV"?

08:42.500 --> 08:45.000
Alisha sent this e-mail
to her boss, Tim Waterbend,

08:45.000 --> 08:47.170
just hours
before she was fired.

08:47.170 --> 08:48.540
Metro police
on it now, too.

08:48.540 --> 08:49.960
-Good.
-What did you say to them?

08:49.960 --> 08:51.750
I gave them her name,
and they ran a check on her.

08:51.750 --> 08:53.460
Turns out, around the time
Alisha disappeared,

08:53.460 --> 08:56.830
she bought a gun.
That got their attention.

08:56.830 --> 08:59.330
What'd I miss?
-Olivia: Take a look.

08:59.330 --> 09:00.750
Alisha lost her job
last week.

09:00.750 --> 09:02.580
She sent an e-mail
to her boss,

09:02.580 --> 09:06.120
telling him she "wouldn't tell
anyone what happened."

09:08.670 --> 09:09.960
You guys notice the part

09:09.960 --> 09:12.120
where she asks her boss
not to "GFV" her?

09:12.120 --> 09:13.670
Does that mean
something to you?

09:13.670 --> 09:15.120
I'm gonna
show you something.

09:15.120 --> 09:17.540
They call it
the "fresh meat" list.

09:17.540 --> 09:19.880
It's a list of all the
attractive female interns

09:19.880 --> 09:21.250
on the Hill.
-Oh, a hot list.

09:23.170 --> 09:24.380
What?
I didn't invent the term.

09:24.380 --> 09:26.330
That's what we called it
when I was in college.

09:26.330 --> 09:28.290
You know,
before the Internet.

09:28.290 --> 09:29.670
I got sent the link
anonymously

09:29.670 --> 09:31.500
when I first started
at the White House.

09:31.500 --> 09:33.420
Dudes use their initials
to log "reviews"

09:33.420 --> 09:34.790
for interns they, uh...

09:34.790 --> 09:36.250
We get it.

09:36.250 --> 09:37.210
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

09:37.210 --> 09:39.040
Still up and running.
Unbelievable.

09:39.040 --> 09:40.540
Is Alisha on here?

09:40.540 --> 09:41.790
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

09:41.790 --> 09:43.040
Bingo.

09:43.040 --> 09:44.250
I still don't
understand what --

09:44.250 --> 09:45.580
GFV, like on a menu.

09:45.580 --> 09:47.420
"Gluten-Free Vegan".

09:47.420 --> 09:48.460
Ugh.

09:50.170 --> 09:51.620
It means
she won't put out.

09:51.620 --> 09:53.460
And if you're one of the guys
on this list

09:53.460 --> 09:55.210
and you get her résumé --
-You won't hire her.

09:55.210 --> 09:57.830
TW...Tim Waterbend.

09:57.830 --> 10:00.670
[ Keyboard clacking ]

10:00.670 --> 10:02.420
The day after she was fired,

10:02.420 --> 10:04.420
Alisha sent her résumé
to 28 openings

10:04.420 --> 10:06.120
via the .gov
internal jobs listings.

10:06.120 --> 10:07.920
Guess how many responses
she got?

10:07.920 --> 10:09.830
-Ah, don't tell me.
-Zero.

10:11.920 --> 10:14.540
So the gun -- you think
she bought it for revenge?

10:14.540 --> 10:16.750
Girl has a dream
of working in D.C.,

10:16.750 --> 10:19.920
girl lands coveted internship
at Congressman's office,

10:19.920 --> 10:21.420
Congressman's Chief of Staff
fires girl

10:21.420 --> 10:22.750
because she won't sleep
with him.

10:22.750 --> 10:24.250
Girl buys gun,
girl disappears.

10:24.250 --> 10:26.000
There's only a handful of ways
this story ends.

10:26.000 --> 10:29.080
And none of them are good.

10:29.080 --> 10:31.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

10:31.250 --> 10:33.210
And the Democrats are, well
[Sighs] they haven't even

10:33.210 --> 10:34.960
made clear their precise
issues with the budget.

10:34.960 --> 10:36.540
I think they want us
to go into a shutdown.

10:36.540 --> 10:38.170
Of course they do.

10:38.170 --> 10:40.460
And they'll say it's because we
were unwilling to compromise.

10:40.460 --> 10:42.000
Mm. [ Gasps ]

10:42.000 --> 10:43.750
How'd you throw it out?

10:43.750 --> 10:44.830
[ Sighs ]

10:44.830 --> 10:48.460
Just stress, I think.

10:48.460 --> 10:50.830
So you want me
to talk to some folks?

10:50.830 --> 10:52.290
Would you?

10:52.290 --> 10:54.170
I know how in demand
you are right now.

10:54.170 --> 10:56.290
It's just
a slow news cycle.

10:56.290 --> 10:58.500
I'd be happy to whip
some Dems into shape.

10:58.500 --> 10:59.790
[ Sighs ]

10:59.790 --> 11:03.500
Cyrus...I'm so glad
you're all right.

11:03.500 --> 11:05.120
[ Sighs ]

11:05.120 --> 11:07.290
I wanted to
apologize directly for --

11:07.290 --> 11:10.080
Madam President, you have
nothing to apologize for.

11:10.080 --> 11:12.880
If we hadn't regained
control of that plane,

11:12.880 --> 11:15.040
shooting it down would've
been the right decision.

11:15.040 --> 11:16.330
The only decision.

11:16.330 --> 11:17.880
I would've done the same
if I were you.

11:17.880 --> 11:19.500
[ Sighs ]

11:19.500 --> 11:20.880
♪♪

11:20.880 --> 11:22.250
Thank you.

11:22.250 --> 11:23.880
Thank you
for understanding.

11:23.880 --> 11:25.830
You get some rest.

11:25.830 --> 11:26.830
I will.

11:26.830 --> 11:28.500
And, Cyrus?

11:28.500 --> 11:31.170
We are going to figure out
who hijacked that plane.

11:31.170 --> 11:32.620
There will be justice.

11:32.620 --> 11:34.080
I believe it.

11:39.290 --> 11:40.830
VPs are used to taking
a back seat,

11:40.830 --> 11:42.790
but America's put you
in the spotlight.

11:42.790 --> 11:45.210
How are you planning to spend
all this new political capital?

11:45.210 --> 11:46.920
I'm focused on one thing --

11:46.920 --> 11:50.170
supporting the agenda of
President Mellie Grant.

11:50.170 --> 11:52.040
This virus they used
to hijack the plane,

11:52.040 --> 11:53.580
there is no way
that the NSA

11:53.580 --> 11:55.540
or any other government agency
developed malware

11:55.540 --> 11:56.960
with this much
code smell.

11:56.960 --> 11:58.380
Cyrus must've
farmed it out.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.170
Which means there's
a money trail. Charlie?

12:00.170 --> 12:02.210
Not his personal account.
No unusual activity.

12:02.210 --> 12:04.250
The assets in Cyrus's blind
trust have not been touched.

12:04.250 --> 12:05.790
Okay, what about secret
off-shore accounts?

12:05.790 --> 12:08.120
I could look into those
and not find anything,

12:08.120 --> 12:09.500
or, you know, we could call it.

12:09.500 --> 12:12.000
Call it? We've been working
on it for like two seconds.

12:12.000 --> 12:13.790
But I've already broken
like seven Federal laws.

12:13.790 --> 12:15.380
Shh!
Where's the painting?

12:15.380 --> 12:17.080
-What painting?
-The Cezanne.

12:17.080 --> 12:18.250
"The Boy in the Red Vest".

12:18.250 --> 12:19.920
The one that Fenton Glackland
gave him.

12:19.920 --> 12:21.920
It's not there.
-Glackland gave him a Cezanne?

12:21.920 --> 12:23.500
A real Cezanne?
That must be worth --

12:23.500 --> 12:25.500
Enough to hire a hacker
to write you

12:25.500 --> 12:27.420
a special Air Force Two
hijacking virus.

12:27.420 --> 12:29.250
And to finance
whatever comes next.

12:29.250 --> 12:31.120
But you have a contact in
the art underworld, don't you?

12:31.120 --> 12:32.790
All right,
I'll give it a shot.

12:32.790 --> 12:36.460
♪♪

12:36.460 --> 12:40.620
♪♪

12:40.620 --> 12:43.040
It's something...isn't it?

12:44.420 --> 12:46.670
A shame I won't be
able to enjoy it.

12:46.670 --> 12:48.120
I don't follow.

12:52.120 --> 12:53.580
She just met
with Abby Whelan.

12:53.580 --> 12:55.040
[ Sighs ]

12:55.040 --> 12:57.500
Olivia Pope is having her
investigate you.

12:57.500 --> 12:58.790
[ Scoffs ] Lonnie --

12:58.790 --> 13:00.460
This is getting
too dangerous.

13:00.460 --> 13:03.580
What if -- What if she finds
your hacker?

13:03.580 --> 13:05.290
What if she finds me?

13:05.290 --> 13:06.750
You haven't done
anything wrong.

13:06.750 --> 13:09.750
You paid me with a Cezanne so
there wouldn't be a money trail.

13:09.750 --> 13:13.290
Don't tell me I haven't done
anything wrong.

13:13.290 --> 13:16.500
John Adams was a farmer who
just wanted to be a good lawyer.

13:16.500 --> 13:18.580
George Washington's
greatest wish

13:18.580 --> 13:22.210
was a royal commission
to the British army.

13:22.210 --> 13:24.750
No one sets out
to be a revolutionary.

13:24.750 --> 13:27.380
Not at first. Sometimes history
doesn't give you a choice.

13:27.380 --> 13:29.710
The Founding Fathers,
Mr. Vice President?

13:29.710 --> 13:30.920
Really?

13:30.920 --> 13:32.460
Why not?
They were just men.

13:32.460 --> 13:34.500
Men like us
who saw a corrupt system

13:34.500 --> 13:36.040
and had to do something
about it.

13:37.620 --> 13:40.210
You've got a job to do.
An important job.

13:40.210 --> 13:42.670
Worry about that.

13:42.670 --> 13:45.880
Let me worry
about Olivia Pope.

13:45.880 --> 13:51.460
♪♪

13:51.460 --> 13:53.620
[ Door opens ]

13:53.620 --> 13:55.710
I'm sorry, I don't know
an Allison Franklin.

13:55.710 --> 13:57.330
Alisha Francis.

13:57.330 --> 13:59.250
[ Phone beeps ]
She was your intern
in your office.

13:59.250 --> 14:01.040
Maybe it would help if you saw
her name in print.

14:01.040 --> 14:03.380
What do you mean?

14:03.380 --> 14:04.750
See? He remembers.

14:04.750 --> 14:06.540
-Where did you get that?
-I don't see how that matters.

14:06.540 --> 14:08.000
All I see is the name
of a missing girl

14:08.000 --> 14:09.420
with your initials
stamped right next to it.

14:09.420 --> 14:11.210
[ Phone beeps ]
Initials?

14:11.210 --> 14:13.290
Please. You don't know what
you're talking about.

14:13.290 --> 14:14.420
Yes, we do, and you know
that we do,

14:14.420 --> 14:16.250
which is why you haven't
even glanced at your phone

14:16.250 --> 14:17.420
once in the last
thirty seconds,

14:17.420 --> 14:18.830
even though it's been beeping
incessantly.

14:18.830 --> 14:20.170
[ Phone beeps ]

14:22.460 --> 14:23.750
It's not my fault.

14:23.750 --> 14:25.670
If she didn't want
to play the game, that's on her,

14:25.670 --> 14:28.500
but I'm not responsible --
-Not responsible?

14:28.500 --> 14:30.750
You ruined a woman's life,
destroyed her career,

14:30.750 --> 14:32.920
because she wouldn't
sleep with you.

14:32.920 --> 14:35.040
You think I cared about that?
You have the list.

14:35.040 --> 14:37.000
I'm not hurting here,
okay?

14:37.000 --> 14:38.670
But there is a way
the game is played.

14:38.670 --> 14:40.790
Everybody knows that.
She knows that.

14:40.790 --> 14:43.170
I never told anyone
not to hire her,

14:43.170 --> 14:44.750
but if she had made
some better choices --

14:44.750 --> 14:45.830
Where is she?

14:45.830 --> 14:47.330
I told you, I don't know.

14:47.330 --> 14:48.790
No, you didn't.

14:48.790 --> 14:50.460
You told me
you didn't know her,

14:50.460 --> 14:52.290
and that was a lie,
but you can try to tell me that

14:52.290 --> 14:53.580
now if you want,
and I won't believe it,

14:53.580 --> 14:54.790
because
I know about the gun.

14:54.790 --> 14:56.080
What?

14:56.080 --> 14:57.330
[ Whispering ]
Alisha bought a gun.

14:57.330 --> 14:59.880
And if I had to guess,
I'd say it's because

14:59.880 --> 15:02.670
she knows who's responsible
for screwing up her life.

15:02.670 --> 15:03.880
That's insane.

15:03.880 --> 15:05.790
Maybe, but it's what
I would've done.

15:05.790 --> 15:07.460
[ Phone beeps ]
So, I don't know

15:07.460 --> 15:09.920
if she wanted to hurt you, or if
she just wanted to scare you,

15:09.920 --> 15:12.170
but whatever happened, clearly
it didn't go the way she planned

15:12.170 --> 15:14.830
because you're still here
and she's not...
[ Phone beeping ]

15:14.830 --> 15:16.790
which, as far as I'm concerned,
is the injustice of the century.

15:16.790 --> 15:18.540
And for the love of God,
would you just put your phone

15:18.540 --> 15:19.460
on vibrate
like a normal person!

15:19.460 --> 15:20.790
Liv.

15:20.790 --> 15:22.580
It's not his.

15:22.580 --> 15:23.750
It's mine.

15:23.750 --> 15:29.120
♪♪

15:29.120 --> 15:35.120
♪♪

15:35.420 --> 15:40.040
So, Waterbend's not just
a sleaze, he's a murderer.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.960
Do they think he used
her own gun against her --

15:42.960 --> 15:43.880
He didn't kill her.

15:43.880 --> 15:45.500
Excuse me?

15:45.500 --> 15:47.580
It was suicide, Liv.
That's why she bought the gun.

15:49.580 --> 15:51.880
She killed herself.

15:52.920 --> 15:57.580
♪♪

15:57.580 --> 16:02.330
♪♪

16:02.330 --> 16:06.500
[ Voice breaking ]
She just, uh...

16:06.500 --> 16:09.460
never said anything.

16:09.460 --> 16:13.330
And do something like this,
hurt herself in this way...

16:13.330 --> 16:15.000
[ Sobs ]

16:15.000 --> 16:16.580
She could've talked to me.

16:18.120 --> 16:21.040
To think
that she felt so alone.

16:22.620 --> 16:24.120
[ Sighs ]

16:24.120 --> 16:26.290
This town...

16:26.290 --> 16:28.670
these monsters.

16:28.670 --> 16:30.170
[ Sighs ]

16:31.670 --> 16:33.920
And you.

16:35.290 --> 16:37.750
You think I don't know
who you really are?

16:37.750 --> 16:39.750
I watch the news.

16:39.750 --> 16:44.210
I know about your...
relationship with Grant.

16:44.210 --> 16:48.460
Oh, you're at the top
of the heap,

16:48.460 --> 16:52.380
and everyone knows who
you screwed to get there.

16:52.380 --> 16:55.290
Gary...I understand
that you're hurting,

16:55.290 --> 16:56.460
but that's not --

16:56.460 --> 16:58.830
She was here
because of you.

16:58.830 --> 17:02.290
But you are not
a role model.

17:02.290 --> 17:05.080
But my daughter
couldn't see that.

17:05.080 --> 17:08.920
She couldn't see
how disgusting this place is,

17:08.920 --> 17:11.500
and how you fit right in.

17:11.500 --> 17:13.420
Because she was good.

17:13.420 --> 17:16.000
She was a good person.

17:16.000 --> 17:18.000
She was better than you...

17:18.000 --> 17:20.330
♪♪

17:20.330 --> 17:22.920
...and she wouldn't play
this sick game.

17:22.920 --> 17:25.670
And she died because of it.

17:25.670 --> 17:30.540
She followed you into the swamp,
and it sucked her under.

17:30.540 --> 17:35.710
♪♪

17:42.080 --> 17:43.790
We can't just let this go.
Alisha deserves justice.

17:43.790 --> 17:45.170
Waterbend might not
have killed her,

17:45.170 --> 17:46.670
but he's not innocent.
We have to do something.

17:46.670 --> 17:48.880
We have to do something for
every woman on this list.

17:48.880 --> 17:50.500
Behavior like this
is allowed to fester

17:50.500 --> 17:52.170
because those in power
allow it to.

17:52.170 --> 17:54.710
I'm here, yes. Absolutely, I'll
take any time you can give me.

17:54.710 --> 17:56.920
Yes, and?
And so maybe
I talk to their bosses.

17:56.920 --> 17:58.210
-You're kidding.
-Five minutes is fine,

17:58.210 --> 17:59.580
although I'd love 10.
-I'm not.

17:59.580 --> 18:02.830
This town is one big,
endless frat party

18:02.830 --> 18:04.250
with zero accountability.

18:04.250 --> 18:06.290
Don't tell me their bosses,
men of your generation,

18:06.290 --> 18:08.120
are any better,
and what moral high ground

18:08.120 --> 18:09.460
do you think you have,
anyway?

18:09.460 --> 18:10.830
I'm on the books.

18:10.830 --> 18:13.040
Talked my way into 15 minutes
with the President.

18:13.040 --> 18:15.380
If we can get her
to consider legislation --

18:15.380 --> 18:17.920
That'd be great for the future,
but it won't do much

18:17.920 --> 18:20.080
for the problem
in front of us right now.

18:20.080 --> 18:21.960
This shouldn't be that
difficult.

18:21.960 --> 18:24.830
We have a list that proves
these men abused their power.

18:24.830 --> 18:26.960
Shouldn't this be enough
of a smoking gun on its own?

18:26.960 --> 18:28.460
It should be,
but it isn't.

18:28.460 --> 18:30.040
[ Sighs ]

18:37.580 --> 18:39.210
[ Papers rustle ]

18:42.830 --> 18:45.000
What is it?

18:47.500 --> 18:49.790
Your name
is on the list, too.

18:49.790 --> 18:52.080
T.W. ranked you
a "Prime Rib".

18:52.080 --> 18:54.500
I assume
that's Tim Waterbend?

18:54.500 --> 18:58.500
Meghan, when Tim Waterbend
took you to dinner last month,

18:58.500 --> 19:01.790
did he make it explicit
that you wouldn't be hired

19:01.790 --> 19:04.040
unless you slept with him?

19:06.420 --> 19:08.380
I'd had a couple drinks.

19:08.380 --> 19:11.670
I figured it'd be easier
to just put up with it.

19:11.670 --> 19:13.210
You know these guys.

19:13.210 --> 19:16.620
If you reject them, they get
so...butt-hurt about it.

19:16.620 --> 19:18.380
I know exactly.

19:18.380 --> 19:20.960
Because this rejected man --
your boss --

19:20.960 --> 19:22.580
used the fresh meat list

19:22.580 --> 19:24.920
to make sure Alisha would never
work in Washington again.

19:24.920 --> 19:26.710
Because she wouldn't
sleep with him?!

19:26.710 --> 19:29.460
The good news is we can use
this list to build a case

19:29.460 --> 19:31.420
against the man
who fired her.

19:31.420 --> 19:33.670
But it would help
if some of the other women

19:33.670 --> 19:35.620
whose names
appear on the list

19:35.620 --> 19:38.290
were willing to corroborate
these kinds of details.

19:38.290 --> 19:40.120
♪♪

19:40.120 --> 19:42.790
You want me to out
this pig as a pig.

19:42.790 --> 19:44.380
♪♪

19:44.380 --> 19:46.170
Ruin his career.

19:46.170 --> 19:48.330
But what happens
to my career?

19:48.330 --> 19:50.710
I don't know.
But at least, unlike Alisha,

19:50.710 --> 19:52.540
you'll still have
your life.

19:52.540 --> 19:55.330
If nobody finds the courage
to take these men on,

19:55.330 --> 19:58.210
they're just gonna keep doing
what they've been doing.

19:58.210 --> 20:01.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

20:03.040 --> 20:05.460
Even more disturbing
than what's in that folder

20:05.460 --> 20:07.460
is what happens
to staffers on the Hill

20:07.460 --> 20:09.250
when they try to report
workplace harassment

20:09.250 --> 20:10.460
to her or his boss.

20:10.460 --> 20:11.710
Oh, I know.

20:11.710 --> 20:14.290
When I was a Senator, every
female knew it by heart.

20:14.290 --> 20:16.170
30 days counseling,
30 days mediation,

20:16.170 --> 20:18.170
meaning confrontations
with your harasser

20:18.170 --> 20:20.250
and not-so-veiled threats
by your harasser

20:20.250 --> 20:22.380
and their very powerful
legal defense team.

20:22.380 --> 20:24.330
The odds are immediately
stacked against you.

20:24.330 --> 20:26.170
And if you're
a woman of color?

20:26.170 --> 20:28.000
Mm.

20:28.000 --> 20:30.710
All that's left for these women
is a non-disclosure agreement,

20:30.710 --> 20:32.420
a ruined career,
and then it's...

20:32.420 --> 20:34.540
-Back to business as usual.
-Yes.

20:34.540 --> 20:37.330
We have to do something
about this, Madam President.

20:37.330 --> 20:39.670
The way to truly prevent
harassment

20:39.670 --> 20:42.710
is to incorporate a punitive
clause into any new legislation.

20:42.710 --> 20:44.380
[ Chuckles ]
That's great.

20:44.380 --> 20:47.460
[ Scoffs ] Well, ideally
it's great, but realistically?

20:47.460 --> 20:50.000
You're asking me to propose a
bill that would punish

20:50.000 --> 20:52.380
many of the lawmakers
who would need to pass it.

20:52.380 --> 20:55.460
They would scour that bill
and find enough flaws

20:55.460 --> 20:57.620
that it would never even
make it to my desk.

20:57.620 --> 20:59.290
What about
an executive order?

20:59.290 --> 21:01.750
Congress would insinuate
that I was abusing my power

21:01.750 --> 21:03.540
for a personal cause.

21:03.540 --> 21:06.120
[ Sighs ] I can't do it.

21:09.580 --> 21:12.170
You can't,
or you don't want to?

21:13.670 --> 21:16.120
Marcus --
Come on, there's got to
be a way for us to --

21:16.120 --> 21:18.170
I'm sure there is a way.
This just may not be it.

21:18.170 --> 21:19.620
Maybe you don't want to put
forth the effort

21:19.620 --> 21:21.290
to make it happen.
-Just because you are not

21:21.290 --> 21:23.000
getting what you want,
don't accuse me --

21:23.000 --> 21:25.040
Oh, Mellie, when it comes to
you, I never get what I want.

21:28.830 --> 21:33.580
♪♪

21:33.580 --> 21:38.880
♪♪

21:38.880 --> 21:40.920
Thank you for coming,
Marcus.

21:40.920 --> 21:43.710
♪♪

21:43.710 --> 21:47.500
I will take your proposal
into consideration.

21:47.500 --> 21:51.620
♪♪

21:51.620 --> 21:56.830
♪♪

21:56.830 --> 21:58.790
[ Door opens, shuts ]

21:58.790 --> 22:03.210
♪♪

22:03.210 --> 22:05.000
[ Gasps ]

22:05.000 --> 22:07.250
[ Groans ]

22:07.250 --> 22:09.040
[ Sighs ]

22:11.750 --> 22:12.920
What's so funny?

22:12.920 --> 22:15.460
Cyrus sent me a thing.
Look.

22:15.460 --> 22:18.210
Cyrus Beene bobbleheads.
-You guys are texting?

22:18.210 --> 22:20.790
On and off.
Is that my lo mein?

22:20.790 --> 22:22.620
Hey, you don't have
anything to do

22:22.620 --> 22:25.380
with this pervy spreadsheet
that's going around, do you?

22:25.380 --> 22:26.790
Pervy spreadsheet?

22:26.790 --> 22:29.750
There's a list going around
Congress ranking female interns.

22:29.750 --> 22:31.540
Some girl
killed herself over it.

22:31.540 --> 22:33.750
I think Liv's working with
the dad to sort it out.

22:33.750 --> 22:36.920
So, you and Cyrus, you guys
are like friends now?

22:36.920 --> 22:39.460
Brothers in arms, Abby.
We cheated death together.

22:39.460 --> 22:41.460
Has he been asking
about the investigation?

22:41.460 --> 22:43.750
What do you mean?
Like whether or not
you guys have any suspects,

22:43.750 --> 22:45.080
that kind of thing.
-Not really.

22:45.080 --> 22:46.540
Even if he did,
I wouldn't know anything.

22:46.540 --> 22:48.620
You're the Attorney General
of the United States.

22:48.620 --> 22:50.750
That's correct. But in the case
of the hijacking,

22:50.750 --> 22:52.830
I'm also a witness.
It's a conflict of interest.

22:52.830 --> 22:55.380
You recused yourself?
-I had to.

22:55.380 --> 22:57.500
-Recused himself?
-He's a potential witness.

22:57.500 --> 22:59.380
Conflicting out David
could have been

22:59.380 --> 23:01.080
part of Cyrus' plan
from the beginning.

23:01.080 --> 23:03.330
What'd you get from Lola?
-Lola was a dead end,

23:03.330 --> 23:04.670
but she does have a Chagall
available

23:04.670 --> 23:06.380
if anyone's got a couple million
lying around.

23:06.380 --> 23:08.250
Was there anything
on the darknet?

23:08.250 --> 23:10.540
Nope, and I haven't had any luck
tying Cyrus to the malware.

23:12.080 --> 23:13.380
Hmm.

23:13.380 --> 23:14.880
Is that a good "hmm"
or a bad "hmm"?

23:14.880 --> 23:17.170
Could be nothing, but I just
found a draft of his speech

23:17.170 --> 23:18.920
for the Al Smith dinner
on Cyrus' computer.

23:18.920 --> 23:20.750
The Al Smith dinner?
That was the same day

23:20.750 --> 23:22.210
Air Force Two was hijacked.
-Hold up.

23:22.210 --> 23:24.120
Didn't you say that he asked
to go to that pirate summit?

23:24.120 --> 23:25.250
Why would he waste
his time

23:25.250 --> 23:26.420
writing a speech
for this other thing?

23:26.420 --> 23:28.040
According to his calendar's
metadata,

23:28.040 --> 23:30.120
he was supposed to go to
the Al Smith dinner last night,

23:30.120 --> 23:31.670
and the summit was dumped
on him last-minute.

23:31.670 --> 23:33.380
All right, so let me
get this straight.

23:33.380 --> 23:35.080
We can't prove that Cyrus
sold the painting,

23:35.080 --> 23:37.460
we can't tie him to the virus,
and he wasn't even supposed to

23:37.460 --> 23:38.880
be on the plane
when it all went down.

23:38.880 --> 23:40.960
So tell me again why we're
wasting our time with this?

23:40.960 --> 23:42.880
I hate to admit it, Abby,
but Charlie's right.

23:42.880 --> 23:44.380
-Thank you?
-Did David say anything else

23:44.380 --> 23:46.500
that could be helpful to us?

23:50.620 --> 23:53.620
It wasn't David.
It was Liv.

23:53.620 --> 23:56.170
Liv?
She said he all
but admitted it to her.

23:56.170 --> 23:57.580
-Liv said?
-I'm sorry, but --

23:57.580 --> 23:58.920
-Shut it down!
-You wouldn't have

23:58.920 --> 24:00.620
gone along with it
if I had told you the truth.

24:00.620 --> 24:02.330
We're done!
Take the board down now.

24:02.330 --> 24:04.880
I know I messed up. I know.
But this is not about Liv.

24:04.880 --> 24:06.580
Of course it is!

24:06.580 --> 24:08.670
Everything Olivia Pope does
is about Olivia Pope.

24:08.670 --> 24:09.960
She used you, Abby.

24:09.960 --> 24:11.540
David almost died
on that plane.

24:11.540 --> 24:13.380
And I almost died
in a basement.

24:13.380 --> 24:15.000
I am not going down
another rabbit hole

24:15.000 --> 24:16.880
that could end with one of us
actually dead.

24:16.880 --> 24:18.040
Not for Olivia,
not anymore.

24:18.040 --> 24:20.620
♪♪

24:20.620 --> 24:22.920
[ Door opens, closes ]

24:26.040 --> 24:27.920
Cyrus did good
with Mais and Regnier,

24:27.920 --> 24:30.670
but Stowell and Clinesmith
and a few others aren't budging.

24:30.670 --> 24:32.500
If we don't make some changes
to the budget,

24:32.500 --> 24:33.540
a shutdown is inevitable.

24:33.540 --> 24:34.830
So much for getting
an early night.

24:34.830 --> 24:36.580
Oh. Mm.

24:36.580 --> 24:38.670
[ Sighs ]

24:38.670 --> 24:39.920
We'll make it fun.

24:39.920 --> 24:41.420
-Fun?
-Yeah.

24:41.420 --> 24:43.420
We'll have the kitchen
make us some fried chicken,

24:43.420 --> 24:45.040
get you a hot pad
for your back,

24:45.040 --> 24:47.420
and delve into the finer points
of corporate tax law.

24:47.420 --> 24:49.790
I think you and I have very
different ideas about fun.

24:49.790 --> 24:51.880
Oh, tell me, what would you
rather focus on

24:51.880 --> 24:54.460
than exemptions and deductions
and discretionary spending?

24:54.460 --> 24:56.710
Actually...

24:56.710 --> 24:59.620
since you asked...

24:59.620 --> 25:02.830
I'm thinking of introducing
legislation

25:02.830 --> 25:05.000
addressing how this country
handles sexual harassment

25:05.000 --> 25:07.040
in the workplace,
starting right here on the Hill.

25:09.040 --> 25:10.920
It's good. Important.

25:10.920 --> 25:12.170
[ Sighs ]

25:12.170 --> 25:13.830
The Democrats
will vote for it,

25:13.830 --> 25:15.540
and then they'll hold it
over your head

25:15.540 --> 25:17.380
when you try to push
this budget through,

25:17.380 --> 25:19.040
forcing you to make
all kinds of compromises

25:19.040 --> 25:21.170
because, hey, they went along
with your harassment bill

25:21.170 --> 25:22.580
even though
they wanted it all along.

25:22.580 --> 25:23.920
And then there's
the Republicans --

25:23.920 --> 25:25.830
-But if we wait --
-If we wait...

25:25.830 --> 25:27.790
it'll be an easy sell.

25:27.790 --> 25:30.210
Tackle it
in a few months...

25:30.210 --> 25:32.000
once this budget's
been safely passed.

25:33.920 --> 25:35.290
[ Scoffs ]

25:37.040 --> 25:38.500
[ Intercom beeps ]

25:38.500 --> 25:41.790
Rachel...we're gonna
need fried chicken.

25:43.000 --> 25:45.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

25:57.290 --> 25:58.580
You have news?

25:59.880 --> 26:03.500
Not about Cyrus, though --
about the team.

26:03.500 --> 26:08.000
They know that it was you
who put me on this.

26:10.210 --> 26:11.880
And?

26:11.880 --> 26:14.960
We're dropping
the investigation.

26:14.960 --> 26:17.210
I couldn't keep
lying to them, Liv.

26:17.210 --> 26:19.960
They're my friends.

26:23.880 --> 26:26.580
[ Siren wails distantly ]

26:26.580 --> 26:28.790
I hear you're working
a case on the Hill.

26:28.790 --> 26:30.670
How's that going?

26:33.500 --> 26:35.670
About as well
as this one.

26:43.380 --> 26:46.620
He's guilty, Abby.

26:46.620 --> 26:48.830
Cyrus did this.

26:48.830 --> 26:51.790
You may be right...

26:51.790 --> 26:54.830
but it can't be us
who proves it.

27:15.670 --> 27:18.500
[ Sighs ]

27:18.500 --> 27:20.380
What if we put
a guarantee

27:20.380 --> 27:23.420
on the funding
for the Vet Affairs program?

27:23.420 --> 27:25.250
Stowell and Clinesmith
have been pushing

27:25.250 --> 27:27.380
that vet assistance bill
for months in committee.

27:27.380 --> 27:29.540
You guarantee funding, they'll
owe you their votes, plus some.

27:29.540 --> 27:32.500
Ah! Two down! Two glasses
of hooch coming up!

27:32.500 --> 27:33.710
[ Gasps ] Oh.

27:33.710 --> 27:35.830
[ Gasping ]

27:35.830 --> 27:37.580
[ Grunts ]

27:37.580 --> 27:38.790
You okay?

27:38.790 --> 27:40.210
[ Groans ]

27:40.210 --> 27:41.670
She will be
after some hooch.

27:41.670 --> 27:42.960
And throw me
the tennis ball, too?

27:42.960 --> 27:44.830
Yep.

27:44.830 --> 27:46.080
Here.
-[ Sighs ]

27:47.420 --> 27:48.960
Ohh.

27:48.960 --> 27:50.290
[ Sighs ]

27:53.040 --> 27:54.210
[ Glass clinks ]

27:55.540 --> 27:57.460
All right.

27:57.460 --> 27:58.580
Oh.

27:58.580 --> 27:59.580
Cheers.

27:59.580 --> 28:00.920
Ah!

28:00.920 --> 28:02.080
[ Painful chuckling ]

28:17.290 --> 28:19.040
You gonna be in fighting shape
to celebrate

28:19.040 --> 28:20.170
when we pass this thing?

28:20.170 --> 28:21.790
I hope so.

28:21.790 --> 28:25.000
If the press gets word that I'm
laid up because of Happy Baby --

28:25.000 --> 28:27.380
I'm sorry.
Happy Baby?

28:27.380 --> 28:29.210
It's a pose.

28:29.210 --> 28:30.830
A yoga pose.

28:30.830 --> 28:34.460
I threw my back out
doing yoga.

28:34.460 --> 28:37.500
Oh, we are definitely not
telling the press that.

28:37.500 --> 28:39.420
I should've known better!

28:39.420 --> 28:42.250
Presidents don't roll themselves
into pretzels.

28:42.250 --> 28:44.420
They run or play tennis

28:44.420 --> 28:47.500
or some other Western,
accident-free activity.

28:47.500 --> 28:49.330
You think running and
tennis are accident-free?

28:49.330 --> 28:50.500
W-well.

28:50.500 --> 28:52.880
1979, Jimmy Carter
tries to run a 10K.

28:52.880 --> 28:55.920
Three miles in, he faints
into the arms of his detail.

28:55.920 --> 28:57.380
-[ Laughs ]
-Bush Sr...

28:57.380 --> 28:59.120
exhausts himself playing
doubles tennis

28:59.120 --> 29:00.670
with the Japanese
prime minister --

29:00.670 --> 29:02.000
which he loses,
by the way --

29:02.000 --> 29:03.330
and then a few hours
later,

29:03.330 --> 29:05.210
he hurls his dinner
into the guy's lap.

29:05.210 --> 29:06.500
In front of
all the press.

29:06.500 --> 29:09.330
[ Laughing ] No, no more,
no more! It hurts, it hurts!

29:09.330 --> 29:11.290
So you're doing just fine
with your Happy Baby.

29:12.620 --> 29:15.170
Oh!

29:16.580 --> 29:17.920
We make a good team,
you and me.

29:17.920 --> 29:19.960
[ Sighs ] Yeah.

29:22.920 --> 29:25.000
[ Sighs ]

29:25.000 --> 29:27.250
[ Giggles ]

29:30.000 --> 29:34.460
♪♪

29:34.460 --> 29:38.670
♪♪

29:38.670 --> 29:43.620
♪♪

29:43.620 --> 29:44.880
Jake, I...

29:44.880 --> 29:46.540
Mellie, I, uh...

29:46.540 --> 29:50.830
I...

29:50.830 --> 29:53.000
I think you should go.

29:53.000 --> 29:57.960
♪♪

29:57.960 --> 30:00.170
[ Groans ]

30:00.170 --> 30:02.170
[ Sighs ]

30:02.170 --> 30:03.580
You need me to help you?

30:03.580 --> 30:05.460
Um...I'm fine.

30:05.460 --> 30:11.120
♪♪

30:11.120 --> 30:12.670
Good night, Madam President.

30:12.670 --> 30:16.000
♪♪

30:16.000 --> 30:18.750
[ Door opens, closes ]

30:18.750 --> 30:24.250
♪♪

30:24.250 --> 30:27.500
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

30:27.500 --> 30:29.040
I was thinking
about grabbing some sandwiches

30:29.040 --> 30:30.120
from the deli up the block.
You want?

30:30.120 --> 30:31.460
Uh, yeah.

30:31.460 --> 30:33.120
What're you working on
over there?

30:33.120 --> 30:34.710
Nothing.

30:34.710 --> 30:38.080
You are not still screwing
around with that virus.

30:38.080 --> 30:39.420
Quinn told us
to drop that.

30:39.420 --> 30:43.920
I know.
But it feels wrong to drop it.

30:43.920 --> 30:45.170
What if the old Liv
is back?

30:45.170 --> 30:46.710
[ Scoffs ] Please.

30:46.710 --> 30:48.170
You've seen what
she's been doing

30:48.170 --> 30:49.750
since she left
the White House.

30:49.750 --> 30:51.500
Maybe she's --
maybe she's coming back.

30:51.500 --> 30:53.040
The old Liv is dead!

30:54.670 --> 30:57.080
There's no coming back
after what she's done.

30:57.080 --> 31:00.040
No resurrection and
life-everlasting hallelujah.

31:00.040 --> 31:03.460
Maybe she's try--
The only thing that matters
to Liv is the White House.

31:03.460 --> 31:05.670
She doesn't care
about justice.

31:05.670 --> 31:08.210
All she cares about is getting
back on Mellie's good side.

31:08.210 --> 31:09.290
I'm not working for Liv,

31:09.290 --> 31:11.420
and I'm not working
for the White House.

31:11.420 --> 31:14.620
As far as I'm concerned,
the whole thing can burn.

31:14.620 --> 31:20.620
♪♪

31:28.380 --> 31:30.420
You okay?

31:32.620 --> 31:34.670
We just need one --

31:34.670 --> 31:36.920
just one of these women
to come forward.

31:36.920 --> 31:38.120
I know.

31:40.040 --> 31:42.000
[ Sighs ]

31:44.460 --> 31:46.500
Hey.

31:46.500 --> 31:49.120
Did I...

31:49.120 --> 31:51.330
when we first met --

31:51.330 --> 31:52.620
On the campaign trail?

31:52.620 --> 31:53.750
Yeah.

31:56.830 --> 31:58.460
What about it?

31:59.830 --> 32:01.620
Was I...

32:01.620 --> 32:03.880
What?

32:03.880 --> 32:05.920
I don't know.

32:05.920 --> 32:08.120
♪♪

32:08.120 --> 32:09.710
Inappropriate?

32:09.710 --> 32:12.120
♪♪

32:12.120 --> 32:14.540
-You're asking if --
-Yes.

32:14.540 --> 32:16.170
I mean it.

32:16.170 --> 32:18.210
Really?
You're asking if you and I --

32:18.210 --> 32:20.210
Did I cross a line?

32:20.210 --> 32:23.330
I just want to know.

32:23.330 --> 32:28.880
♪♪

32:28.880 --> 32:30.920
No.

32:30.920 --> 32:32.750
♪♪

32:32.750 --> 32:35.120
That was different.
We crossed that line together.

32:37.210 --> 32:39.170
Do you regret it?

32:39.170 --> 32:45.170
♪♪

32:45.670 --> 32:47.420
No.

32:47.420 --> 32:50.380
♪♪

32:50.380 --> 32:52.960
I would
cross that line again.

32:52.960 --> 32:57.920
♪♪

32:57.920 --> 32:59.120
[ Footsteps approaching ]

32:59.120 --> 33:02.080
-Look who stopped by.
-Meghan.

33:02.080 --> 33:04.500
Hi.

33:04.500 --> 33:06.580
I'm in.

33:06.580 --> 33:09.960
♪♪

33:09.960 --> 33:13.670
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

33:13.670 --> 33:16.380
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:16.380 --> 33:18.380
Um...

33:18.380 --> 33:20.670
[ Whitney Houston's "I Believe
In You And Me" plays ]

33:20.670 --> 33:24.080
♪♪

33:24.080 --> 33:27.210
I'm here today to talk
about the death

33:27.210 --> 33:30.460
of my friend and co-worker,
Alisha Francis.

33:30.460 --> 33:33.540
A week ago,
Alisha lost her job.

33:33.540 --> 33:36.670
A few days later,

33:36.670 --> 33:39.290
she took her own life.

33:39.290 --> 33:41.420
Before she was fired,

33:41.420 --> 33:45.880
Alisha made a courageous,
professional choice --

33:45.880 --> 33:48.880
one that, for her...

33:48.880 --> 33:54.250
♪ You will always be the one ♪

33:54.250 --> 33:56.330
...ended in tragedy.

33:56.330 --> 34:00.000
Her choice was to decline
to perform sexual favors

34:00.000 --> 34:02.920
for a man who had the power
to help or hurt her

34:02.920 --> 34:04.830
in her chosen career.

34:04.830 --> 34:06.210
♪ I believe in dreams again ♪

34:06.210 --> 34:09.170
He punished her
for that choice,

34:09.170 --> 34:12.040
not just with the loss
of her job,

34:12.040 --> 34:16.040
but with a devastating assault
on her professional reputation.

34:16.040 --> 34:21.170
If you're asking yourselves
how I know all this,

34:21.170 --> 34:23.790
it's because I had
the same choice to make,

34:23.790 --> 34:25.710
and I chose differently.

34:25.710 --> 34:29.120
I had sex with this man,

34:29.120 --> 34:30.920
and just as he promised,

34:30.920 --> 34:33.920
I was rewarded
with a permanent position.

34:33.920 --> 34:37.960
I don't relish standing
up here to discuss my sex life,

34:37.960 --> 34:40.960
but I see no other way
to expose a culture

34:40.960 --> 34:43.790
where women cannot
succeed on their own merits,

34:43.790 --> 34:47.040
but are instead judged
by their attractiveness

34:47.040 --> 34:49.210
and their sexual compliance.

34:49.210 --> 34:51.830
Ms. Seeley's statement
has prompted an outpouring

34:51.830 --> 34:54.420
of similar stories from
other female Hill staffers --

34:54.420 --> 34:57.000
some dating as far back
as the 1980s.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.540
And a group of these women
has even turned the tables

34:59.540 --> 35:02.380
on predatory men,
compiling a counter-list

35:02.380 --> 35:05.250
of D.C.'s worst
sexual offenders.

35:05.250 --> 35:09.620
♪♪

35:09.620 --> 35:10.750
That was incredible.

35:10.750 --> 35:12.330
Olivia:
Meghan was very brave.

35:12.330 --> 35:13.960
I told you
we only needed one.

35:13.960 --> 35:16.330
Yes, you are very smart.

35:16.330 --> 35:18.250
Would you like
your gold star now?

35:18.250 --> 35:21.170
Seriously, I know
there's so much more to do,

35:21.170 --> 35:23.790
and I'm willing to help
in any way I can.

35:23.790 --> 35:26.000
Thank you. I agree.

35:26.000 --> 35:28.620
♪♪

35:28.620 --> 35:30.380
I'll be in touch.

35:30.380 --> 35:34.500
♪♪

35:34.500 --> 35:39.960
♪ 'Cause I believe in you
and me ♪

35:39.960 --> 35:42.040
Don't be a stranger,
Olivia Pope.

35:42.040 --> 35:44.670
♪♪

35:50.210 --> 35:51.580
Thank you.

35:51.580 --> 35:53.920
[ Sighs ]

35:53.920 --> 35:56.080
Madam President.

35:56.080 --> 35:58.210
I'm announcing my intention
later this afternoon

35:58.210 --> 36:00.620
to pursue legislation tackling
workplace sexual harassment.

36:00.620 --> 36:02.290
I thought
that you should know.

36:02.290 --> 36:04.960
-I thought we agreed that --
-We didn't agree on anything.

36:04.960 --> 36:07.080
You gave me your opinion,
I had a different one,

36:07.080 --> 36:08.620
which is that
you should do your job

36:08.620 --> 36:12.250
and help me both get my budget
and pass my legislation.

36:12.250 --> 36:14.330
Is that something
you're capable of?

36:16.500 --> 36:18.960
Madam President, I'd like to
apologize for last night.

36:18.960 --> 36:20.290
Clearly, I misread
the situation.

36:20.290 --> 36:22.380
Look, Jake.

36:22.380 --> 36:24.880
[ Sighs ]
It's two things.

36:24.880 --> 36:29.880
One, I am not starting an affair
in the Oval with a subordinate,

36:29.880 --> 36:32.540
which, let me remind you --
despite our friendship,

36:32.540 --> 36:35.420
despite the fact that we make a
"good team" -- is what you are.

36:35.420 --> 36:37.250
I will not be another
Fitzgerald Grant

36:37.250 --> 36:38.960
and Olivia Pope,
nor am I interested

36:38.960 --> 36:41.670
in sleeping with someone
who has slept with Olivia Pope.

36:41.670 --> 36:43.790
I know far too much
about where you've been --

36:43.790 --> 36:45.710
That's two things.
Is there anything else?

36:45.710 --> 36:47.210
Yes, actually.

36:47.210 --> 36:49.170
Three --

36:49.170 --> 36:51.790
if this is some kind
of power hunt --

36:51.790 --> 36:55.080
That's where I draw the line.
[ Sighs ]

36:55.080 --> 36:58.250
You may think it's inappropriate
to start something,

36:58.250 --> 37:00.210
you may be
uninterested, fine.

37:00.210 --> 37:04.120
But I have plenty of power
without needing [Sighs]

37:05.880 --> 37:08.210
...I made an advance
because I was attracted to you.

37:08.210 --> 37:09.920
Forgive me.

37:09.920 --> 37:12.290
And do you think
it's lost on me

37:12.290 --> 37:14.080
that this is the week

37:14.080 --> 37:16.330
that you suddenly find yourself
attracted to me,

37:16.330 --> 37:18.420
of all the weeks that we have
known each other?

37:18.420 --> 37:20.420
The one week I need
a little extra help,

37:20.420 --> 37:23.120
the one week that I'm a damsel
in distress --

37:23.120 --> 37:25.830
A damsel in -- I was attracted
to you because it felt good,

37:25.830 --> 37:27.380
us working together.

37:27.380 --> 37:29.330
And when you and Fitz had a good
week working together,

37:29.330 --> 37:30.670
did you hold
his hand, too?

37:32.960 --> 37:34.880
I hope you get well soon,
Madam President.

37:36.670 --> 37:39.460
[ Door opens, closes ]

37:39.460 --> 37:40.920
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

37:40.920 --> 37:43.540
As Washington continues
to reel from recent reports

37:43.540 --> 37:45.670
of widespread sexual
misconduct,

37:45.670 --> 37:47.750
President Mellie Grant has
announced her intentions

37:47.750 --> 37:49.830
of attacking this problem
on a national level.

37:49.830 --> 37:51.920
Analysts consider
the President's move

37:51.920 --> 37:53.250
to be particularly bold

37:53.250 --> 37:55.920
in that she risks
losing support she needs

37:55.920 --> 37:58.750
in order to push along
an already-embattled budget.

37:58.750 --> 38:01.000
[ Knock on door ]

38:01.000 --> 38:03.170
Hi.

38:03.170 --> 38:05.460
Come in.

38:07.500 --> 38:11.790
I just wanted to tell you that
I saw the press conference.

38:11.790 --> 38:13.880
It was good.

38:13.880 --> 38:15.500
Great.

38:17.620 --> 38:19.000
Thanks.

38:22.290 --> 38:26.040
I guess I could've called,
but after all of...

38:26.040 --> 38:30.620
I thought maybe
you wouldn't pick up.

38:30.620 --> 38:32.710
I would've.

38:41.080 --> 38:43.000
I don't blame the team.

38:44.580 --> 38:48.120
I can't because...in the end,

38:48.120 --> 38:50.620
this is not their fight.

38:50.620 --> 38:53.330
♪♪

38:53.330 --> 38:57.120
It's not Quinn's,
it's not yours, it's mine.

38:57.120 --> 39:01.380
I'm the one who needs to step up
because I made Mellie a promise.

39:01.380 --> 39:02.750
At some point or another,

39:02.750 --> 39:04.750
men would try to strip her
of power.

39:04.750 --> 39:08.250
I promised that I wouldn't
stand by and let that happen.

39:08.250 --> 39:14.120
No matter the fallout, no matter
how hard Cyrus pushes back,

39:14.120 --> 39:16.500
I can't let Mellie
stand alone.

39:16.500 --> 39:21.420
♪♪

39:21.420 --> 39:24.120
Well...

39:24.120 --> 39:26.670
I'm in.

39:26.670 --> 39:28.620
Really?

39:28.620 --> 39:30.960
Yeah.

39:32.580 --> 39:35.710
You had me at
dismantling the patriarchy.

39:35.710 --> 39:38.250
♪♪

39:38.250 --> 39:40.500
Okay.

39:40.500 --> 39:42.460
♪♪

39:46.540 --> 39:47.580
Filiz: Sir.

39:47.580 --> 39:49.420
Not a good time.

39:49.420 --> 39:50.580
I know
who made the virus.

39:50.580 --> 39:55.620
♪♪

39:55.620 --> 39:57.540
[ Knock on door ]

39:57.540 --> 39:59.620
What?

39:59.620 --> 40:01.750
[ Sighs ]

40:01.750 --> 40:04.670
Those are the build time-stamps
embedded in the virus's code.

40:04.670 --> 40:05.790
Huck.

40:05.790 --> 40:07.540
It's Charlie's IP address.

40:07.540 --> 40:10.290
The virus was modified
from his laptop.

40:10.290 --> 40:12.670
So what? That virus was on
all of our laptops.

40:12.670 --> 40:15.080
Yeah, but he had it
the day before

40:15.080 --> 40:16.710
it infected Air Force Two.

40:16.710 --> 40:21.210
♪♪

40:21.210 --> 40:23.620
This doesn't
make any sense.

40:23.620 --> 40:26.250
He was against us looking
into this case from the start

40:26.250 --> 40:28.120
because he knew
what we'd find.

40:28.120 --> 40:31.460
He's angry, Quinn.
Really, really angry.

40:31.460 --> 40:36.420
♪♪

40:36.420 --> 40:38.620
There you are. Ready?

40:38.620 --> 40:40.170
What was it?

40:40.170 --> 40:42.790
Some kind
of relapse, hmm?

40:42.790 --> 40:44.880
You got bored
working with the good guys?

40:44.880 --> 40:46.540
Slipped back
into bad habits?

40:46.540 --> 40:48.380
Couldn't resist
an old-school conspiracy?

40:48.380 --> 40:50.500
I don't know
what you're talking about.

40:50.500 --> 40:52.500
Huck traced it.
You wrote that virus.

40:52.500 --> 40:53.920
I did not.

40:53.920 --> 40:55.580
You're working
with Cyrus again.

40:55.580 --> 40:57.250
I'm not.

40:57.250 --> 40:59.920
You don't think I have had
enough lies for the year?!

40:59.920 --> 41:01.880
Look, I don't know what Huck
found, but the hijacking?

41:01.880 --> 41:03.380
I had nothing to do with it.
-[ Scoffs ]

41:03.380 --> 41:05.040
Why would I?
I'm your fiancé.

41:05.040 --> 41:07.460
The father of your child.
I don't need that stuff anymore.

41:07.460 --> 41:09.380
Then how did that virus
end up on your laptop?

41:09.380 --> 41:11.290
How the hell would I know?
Someone must've put it there!

41:13.750 --> 41:15.580
Wait.

41:17.210 --> 41:18.540
Oh, my God.

41:18.540 --> 41:20.920
We need to get you
out of here.

41:20.920 --> 41:22.920
[ Door bangs open ]

41:22.920 --> 41:24.170
Freeze!
Let's see your hands!

41:24.170 --> 41:25.540
-Hands!
-No sudden moves!

41:25.540 --> 41:27.210
Up against the wall.

